
Part (a) Possible Scenarios and how memory is accessed:

Random Scenario- eviction of memory at random across 256 different addresses hard to guage actual efficieny because it is random. The functionality of each as shown in with the hit rate is low and doesnt favor the NRU,NFU, or FIFO because it can not. 

Multiple Localities- A center biased approach that discriminately eliminates the edges mainly while keeping the center. LFU will have an advantage because the center is used more frequently than the edges.

Sequential - Goes from 0-256 in a cyclical manner (not very efficeint premptively) 

Temporal Decay- Uses the swap in swap out system of 12 rotating pages this occurs at a specified larger interval around 333 accesses. 

Hot Spot- A high percentage as assigned a lower percentage of eviction is randomized this is ensure the most accessed are prevented from getting evicted. If only a few pages are frequently used it can work well with low cost.

